        "subject": "LU-5038 llog: do not scan for empty llogs at initialization",
        "message": "LU-5038 llog: do not scan for empty llogs at initialization\n\nin some cases the catalog can contain lots of non-empty llogs\n(e.g. robinhood isn't running all the time and this lead to\nmany alive plain llogs) and scanning this in the context of\nmount can take a lot. instead we can do this during normal\nllog processing.\n\nLustre-commit: dc910ede715c4f13cde0c64d74e7badaa8dcb07b\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/10308\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I0418659e14230c746559d61b411de17a2896e3b0\n"
      },
